'''Fantasy Faction''' is a website and community for fans of [[fantasy]] fiction. They share news, reviews and interviews about books in the [[epic fantasy]], [[sword and sorcery]] and [[heroic fantasy]] genres. It was founded by Marc Aplin<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jofletcherbooks.com/2012/07/wednesday-initiative-blogger-interview-with-marc-aplin-of-fantasy-faction-com/ |title=Wednesday Initiative: Blogger interview with Marc Aplin of Fantasy-Faction.com |publisher=Jo Fletcher Books |date=2012-07-18 |accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref> and Paul Wiseall<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.torbooks.co.uk/blog/2012/07/23/an-exclusive-interview-with-fantasyfaction |title=Exclusive interview with Paul Wiseall of Fantasy Faction |date=2012-07-23 |accessdate=2017-08-25}}</ref> and has won or been nominated for many genre awards:
* [[Reddit]]’s Best Fantasy Website Winner – 2013 and 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/Fantasy/comments/2rh018/best_of_rfantasy_2014_the_results_thread/ |title=Best of /r/fantasy 2014- the RESULTS THREAD! : Fantasy |publisher=Reddit.com |date=2015-01-05 |accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref> * [[World Fantasy Award]] Nomination – 2014<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tor.com/blogs/2014/11/announcing-the-2014-world-fantasy-winners |title=Announcing the 2014 World Fantasy Winners! |publisher=Tor.com |date= |accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref> * [[British Fantasy Award]] Nomination – 2013<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.britishfantasysociety.org/news/british-fantasy-awards-2013-the-nominees/ |title=British Fantasy Awards 2013: the nominees |publisher=The British Fantasy Society |date= |accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref> & 2014<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.locusmag.com/News/2014/06/2014-british-fantasy-award-nominees/ |title=Locus Online News » 2014 British Fantasy Award Nominees |publisher=Locusmag.com |date=2014-06-06 |accessdate=2015-05-14}}</ref> * Angry Robot Blogger Nomination – 2013 * [[Goodreads]]’ Book Blogger Finalist – 2012
