'''Picture lock''' is a stage in [[Film editing|editing a film]] or [[Offline editing|editing a television]] production. It is the stage prior to [[online editing]] when all changes to the film or television program cut have been done and approved. It is then sent to subsequent stages in the process, such as [[online editing]] and [[audio mixing (film and television)|audio mixing]].<ref name="LoBrutto2012">{{cite book|author=Vincent LoBrutto|title=The Art of Motion Picture Editing: An Essential Guide to Methods, Principles, Processes, and Terminology|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=X_4jAgAAQBAJ&pg=PT55|date=1 January 2012|publisher=Allworth Press|isbn=978-1-62153-251-4|pages=55–}}</ref><ref name="McGuireLee2012">{{cite book|author1=Sam McGuire|author2=Paul Lee|title=The Video Editor's Guide to Soundtrack Pro: Workflows, Tools, and Techniques|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UH4rBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA4|date=12 November 2012|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-1-136-05782-3|pages=4–}}</ref><ref name="Holman2012">{{cite book|author=Tomlinson Holman|title=Sound for Film and Television|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gazpAwAAQBAJ&pg=PA164|date=12 November 2012|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-1-136-04610-0|pages=164–}}</ref><ref name="AndersonLucas2016">{{cite book|author1=Kelly Anderson|author2=Martin Lucas|title=Documentary Voice & Vision: A Creative Approach to Non-Fiction Media Production|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DPfdCwAAQBAJ&pg=PA292|date=31 March 2016|publisher=CRC Press|isbn=978-1-317-63613-7|pages=292–}}</ref> Any last minute changes can force portions of subsequent work to be redone.<ref name="Angell2013">{{cite book|author=Dale Angell|title=The Filmmaker's Guide to Final Cut Pro Workflow|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sVAdAAAAQBAJ&pg=PA53|date=18 July 2013|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-136-06062-5|pages=53–}}</ref>

